response:
The domain of the function $$j(x) = \frac{1}{x+8} + \frac{1}{x^2+8} + (\frac{1}{x^3+8})^{-1}$$ is all real numbers except for the values that make the denominator of the function equal to zero. Find the x values that make the function undefined: $$x = -8, -2,-1 and 2$$</think>
<answer>
\begin{align*}
\text{Domain} &= (-\infty,-8)(-8,-2)(-2,-1)\\
&\quad\cup(-1,2) \cup (2,\infty) \\\\\
&= \fbox{$(-\infty,-8)\cup(-8,-2)\cup(-2,-1)\cup (-1,2)\cup (2,\infty)$}
\end{align*}
</answer>

